Class DependencyData

  • java.lang.Object
    • se.jguru.nazgul.core.reflection.api.DependencyData

    public class DependencyData
extends Object
implements Serializable, Comparable<DependencyData>
    Maven dependency information wrapper, as read from a dependency.properties file written by the maven-dependency-plugin.

    • Method Detail

      • getScope

        public String getScope()
        Returns:
        The scope of the dependency whose Group/Artifact/Version coordinates is wrapped by this DependencyData instance. Unless updated, the scope defaults to "compile".

      • setScope

        public void setScope(String scope)
              throws IllegalArgumentException
        Assigns the scope of this DependencyData instance. The scope value should adhere to Maven's dependency scope definition.
        Parameters:
        scope - Should be one of the values compile, provided, runtime, test, system or import.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the scope value was not one of the permitted scopes.
        See Also:
        The Maven Dependency Scopes

      • getType
